<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1497">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/114.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-24">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your February 24. We are very much gratified to receive your
                                assurance that widow or relatives will be permitted to visit
                                cemetery <pb facs="0967" n="851" xml:id="pg_851"/> in company with
                                representative designated by this Government and that exhumation of
                                body will be permitted. We suppose the cemetery is at Juarez.</p>
                            <p>Please ask Villa to permit two American representatives and two
                                British subjects to accompany widow or relatives and urge that after
                                proper examination body be delivered to widow. Request that orders
                                be given so examination may be held with least possible delay.
                                Telegraph reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>